# Priority 2: Performance Optimizations - Implementation Plan

## Goal

Implement performance optimizations to achieve **2-3x faster API response times** and better handle concurrent users on Hostinger shared hosting.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All optimizations must be compatible with shared hosting constraints (no Redis, no custom Apache modules).

---

## Proposed Changes

### Step 4: API Response Caching

#### [NEW] [api/Cache.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/api/Cache.php)

**Purpose:** File-based caching system for API responses

**Features:**
- File-based storage (`/private/cache/`)
- Configurable TTL (Time To Live)
- Cache key generation from request params
- Automatic cache expiration
- Cache invalidation methods
- Cache statistics tracking

**Methods:**
```php
Cache::get($key)              // Retrieve cached data
Cache::set($key, $data, $ttl) // Store data with TTL
Cache::delete($key)           // Invalidate specific cache
Cache::clear()                // Clear all cache
Cache::has($key)              // Check if cached
Cache::stats()                // Get cache statistics
```

---

#### [MODIFY] [api/index.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/api/index.php)

**Changes:**
1. Add `Cache.php` require statement
2. Wrap cacheable endpoints with cache layer
3. Implement cache invalidation on data updates

**Endpoints to Cache:**
- `GET /students` (TTL: 5 minutes)
- `GET /students/{id}` (TTL: 10 minutes)
- `GET /timetable/{personId}` (TTL: 15 minutes)

**Cache Strategy:**
```php
// Before database query
$cacheKey = "students_page_{$page}_limit_{$limit}";
if ($cached = Cache::get($cacheKey)) {
    return $response->write(json_encode($cached));
}

// ... execute database query ...

// After successful query
Cache::set($cacheKey, $result, 300); // 5 minutes
```

