## Performance Targets

### Baseline (Before Optimization)
- API Response Time: 200-500ms
- Database Query Time: 50-150ms
- Cache Hit Rate: 0%
- Concurrent Users: ~10-20

### Target (After Optimization)
- API Response Time: 50-100ms (cached), 150-300ms (uncached)
- Database Query Time: 20-50ms
- Cache Hit Rate: 60-80%
- Concurrent Users: ~50-100

**Overall Improvement:** 2-3x faster ⚡

---

## Rollback Plan

If performance issues arise:

### Step 1: Disable Caching
```php
// In index.php, comment out cache layer
// Cache::set(...);
// if ($cached = Cache::get(...)) { ... }
```

### Step 2: Remove Indexes
```sql
-- Drop added indexes if they cause issues
DROP INDEX idx_status ON gibbonPerson;
DROP INDEX idx_role ON gibbonPerson;
```

### Step 3: Reset OPcache
```bash
# Remove .user.ini
rm /home/u542293952/public_html/backend/.user.ini
```

---

## Implementation Order

1. **Create Cache class** and test independently
2. **Add caching to one endpoint** (students list) and verify
3. **Add caching to remaining endpoints** once proven
4. **Add database indexes** gradually, test after each
5. **Configure OPcache** last (easiest to rollback)

---

## Notes

> [!WARNING]
> Cache invalidation is critical! Ensure cache is cleared when data is updated via:
> - Student enrollment changes
> - Timetable modifications
> - Any POST/PUT/DELETE operations

> [!TIP]
> Monitor cache directory size. With 5-minute TTL, cache should auto-clean, but implement manual cleanup if needed.

